-- New York Jets Invite Phil Simms’s Son for Mini-Camp Tryout
-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 2012-05-01T04:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-01/new-york-jets-invite-phil-simms-s-son-for-mini-camp-tryout.html
The  New York  Jets invited 23 players
to mini-camp for tryouts, including Matt Simms, the younger son
of former New York Giants quarterback Phil Simms, and Harvard
linebacker Josue Ortiz, the  Ivy League ’s co-Player of the Year.  Simms, 23, played in 18 games at quarterback for the
University of Tennessee the past two seasons, including 10
starts, and completed 140 of 257 passes for 1,779 yards and
eight touchdowns, with eight interceptions.  Ortiz was selected the Ivy League’s defensive player of the
year after collecting 10 sacks for Harvard.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
